               <person instant="false"><!--donor-->
                  <persName corresp="PRS0000" instant="false" full="yes">Zä-Wäldä Maryam is mentioned as the commissioner of the Ms. in the subscriptio on fol. 208r and in some supplication formulas (e.g., fols. 160va, 160vb, 161rc, 162rc, 183rc, 197rc, 197va) in the final part of the Ms. In the supplication on fol. 160va, he is mentioned together with "the children of this church" (däqiqä zatti betä krǝstiyan).&#xD;
Some personal names are written over erasures in a secondary hand in the supplication formulas throughout the Ms., most probably to replace the original names of the donors: Täsfa Maryam (e.g., fols. 4vb, 7rb, 7va, 12rb), Zä-Mänfäs Qǝddus (e.g., fols. 7vb, 17ra, 29vb), Wälättä ʾAqlesya (fol. 82vc), Wälättä Ḥǝywät  (e.g., fols. 84rc, 87rb).</persName>
